CEDET

What is CEDET:
CEDET is a Collection of Emacs Development Environment Tools written with the end goal of creating an advanced development environment in Emacs.

Components of CEDET:
EDE
Semantic
SRecode
Cogre
Speedbar
EIEIO

Comparative:
Microsoft's Visual Studio; JBuilder, or Eclipse.

How to install:

How to automatic enable it:

How to use it:

Semantic:
semantic is a program for Emacs which includes, at its core, a lexer, and two compiler compilers (bovinator and wisent). The core utility is the parser infrastructure which allows different types of parsers to be linked into the system. 